# Language policy

## English (required)

- Git commit messages and PR descriptions
- Code: identifiers, types, functions, variables, file names
- Comments and JSDoc in source files
- Scripts: CLI output intended for developers, migration comments, README for developers
- SQL migrations: comments and constraint names

Use conventional commits in English, e.g. `feat(admin): allow branches to cancel orders`.

## Spanish (allowed)

- User-facing copy only: labels, buttons, errors, placeholders, emails, marketing text
- Keep in React components/pages shown to customers and branch staff UI strings
- `es-AR` locale formatting is fine

## Do not

- Mix Spanish in commit messages or code comments going forward
- Rename user-visible Spanish strings to English unless explicitly requested

## When touching legacy Spanish in code

- Translate comments and script logs to English as part of the same change
- Do not change customer-facing Spanish UI unless the task requires it
